17. num dubitamus inventos, i.e. ¹inthe time of Cato, as is clear from the sequence of ideas. The construction of dubito with acc. and infin. (for the negative expression of doubt) belongs to the usage of the Silver Age, and is especially com- mon in Tacitus and Quintilian. It occurs indeed in Livy and Nepos, bnt never in Caesar or Sallust, and in Cicero only in doubtful instances (see note on Quintilian, x. 1, 73).
